Exaggerate: The claim may exaggerate the extent of the economic success in Iowa before COVID-19 by stating that there were more Iowans working than at any other time in history.
Understate: The claim may understate the impact of the COVID-19 pandemic on Iowa's labor force and employment numbers.
Lack enough support: The claim lacks enough support to fully verify the statement, as it only provides limited data from January 2020 and does not consider the subsequent decline in employment due to the pandemic.
Problematic assumption: The claim assumes that the pre-pandemic economic success in Iowa was solely due to the actions of the current administration, without considering other factors or external influences.
Exist alternative explanation: There may be alternative explanations for the increase in employment numbers, such as seasonal fluctuations or temporary factors that may not necessarily indicate long-term economic prosperity.
